---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Boundary from "../components/Boundary.astro";
---

<Base>
  <!-- Hero: calm, serious, hopeful. Mission in two sentences. -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow rise rise-1">The Human-Core Initiative</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title rise rise-2">
        Raising capable, whole humans, from the first months of life to the age
        of AI.
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-lede rise rise-3">
        Human-Core is one free curriculum that gathers the methods the best
        global evidence shows actually work. It begins in infancy with the
        movement, language, and play that build the brain, teaches the
        foundations of reading and mathematics with the methods the evidence
        most strongly supports, adds the human skills school tends to skip, and
        from about age ten teaches children to think with and master AI. The aim
        is children who grow up able and whole, ready to thrive alongside AI
        rather than be displaced by it.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions rise rise-4">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/resources">Explore the curriculum</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/principles">Read the principles</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The two-crisis problem, in brief. -->
  <section class="wrap problem">
    <p class="eyebrow">The problem, in brief</p>
    <h2>Two crises, and they compound.</h2>
    <div class="problem-grid">
      <div class="problem-item">
        <p class="section-no">01</p>
        <h3>Children are not learning the foundations</h3>
        <p>
          The World Bank estimates that around seven in ten 10-year-olds in low-
          and middle-income countries cannot read and understand a simple story,
          a figure that rose from 57% to roughly 70% through the pandemic.
          Wealthy systems are not exempt: foundational skills in reading and
          mathematics are declining across many developed countries too. Too
          often, teaching is unresponsive, and teachers are given almost no
          usable feedback on their own practice.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-item">
        <p class="section-no">02</p>
        <h3>AI changes what learning is for, and how it is avoided</h3>
        <p>
          AI now does most of what the old system trained children for, while
          also giving them a frictionless way to avoid the thinking that builds
          their minds. A system that was already failing to develop children is
          now also obsolete in its aims and newly easy to cheat.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="problem-close">
      This initiative exists to act on both crises at once, in the open,
      globally, rather than to complain about them.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- The boundary: the signature. -->
  <section class="wrap boundary-section">
    <Boundary />
  </section>

  <!-- The three pillars, in one line each. -->
  <section class="wrap pillars-teaser">
    <p class="eyebrow">The three pillars</p>
    <h2>One synthesis, three pieces.</h2>
    <p class="pillars-intro">
      The curriculum is the spine, from infancy onward. The teacher tool serves
      the adults who deliver it. AI mastery is the capstone, built on top once a
      child has the knowledge to judge a machine.
    </p>
    <ol class="pillar-list">
      <li>
        <span class="pillar-n">1</span>
        <div>
          <h3>An open, evidence-based pedagogy</h3>
          <p>
            A complete, age-banded curriculum and methods guide any teacher or
            parent can adopt without permission or payment.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="pillar-n">2</span>
        <div>
          <h3>AI that empowers teachers</h3>
          <p>
            A private, teacher-owned coach that listens to the teaching, not to
            the children's feelings, and turns coaching from a luxury into
            something every teacher can have.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="pillar-n">3</span>
        <div>
          <h3>AI mastery for children</h3>
          <p>
            Teaching children to use AI as a thinking partner they control, to
            audit it for error and bias, and to stay in charge of their own
            minds.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ol>
    <a class="text-link" href="/pillars">Read each pillar in plain language <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
  </section>

  <!-- Where to start -->
  <section class="wrap start">
    <p class="eyebrow">Where to start</p>
    <h2>Find your entry point.</h2>
    <div class="start-grid">
      <a class="start-card" href="/resources/pillar-1-curriculum">
        <span class="start-for">Parents of young children</span>
        <span class="start-title">The early-years foundations</span>
        <span class="start-body">Movement, language, play, and self-regulation, from the first months. Begin at Band A of the curriculum.</span>
      </a>
      <a class="start-card" href="/resources/pillar-1-curriculum">
        <span class="start-for">Primary teachers</span>
        <span class="start-title">The building-years methods</span>
        <span class="start-body">Explicit reading, concrete-to-pictorial-to-abstract mathematics, and teaching each child at their actual level.</span>
      </a>
      <a class="start-card" href="/resources/pillar-3-teacher-workbook">
        <span class="start-for">Teachers of ages ten and up</span>
        <span class="start-title">The AI-mastery capstone</span>
        <span class="start-body">Eight ready-to-run sessions teaching children to use, question, and out-think AI. Runs even without AI in the room.</span>
      </a>
    </div>
    <div class="start-actions">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/resources">Browse all resources</a>
      <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/about">About this work</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding-top: clamp(3.5rem, 8vw, 6.5rem);
    padding-bottom: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem);
  }
  .hero-title {
    font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 6.2vw, 4.3rem);
    max-width: 18ch;
    margin: 1rem 0 0;
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 144, "SOFT" 0;
  }
  .hero-lede {
    font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 2.2vw, 1.45rem);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
    max-width: 40rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }
  .hero-actions { display: flex; gap: 0.9rem; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 2.2rem; }

  section { scroll-margin-top: 6rem; }
  .problem { padding-top: 3.5rem; }
  .problem > h2 { font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.6rem); margin: 0.4rem 0 0; }
  .problem-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 2.5rem;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }
  @media (min-width: 760px) { .problem-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 3rem; } }
  .problem-item h3 {
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    margin: 0.6rem 0 0.7rem;
    max-width: 22ch;
  }
  .problem-item p { color: var(--color-ink-soft); margin: 0; }
  .problem-close {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.3rem, 2.6vw, 1.7rem);
    line-height: 1.4;
    max-width: 36rem;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }

  .boundary-section { margin-top: 4.5rem; }

  .pillars-teaser { margin-top: 4.5rem; }
  .pillars-teaser > h2 { font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.6rem); margin: 0.4rem 0 0; }
  .pillars-intro { color: var(--color-ink-soft); max-width: 44rem; margin: 1rem 0 0; font-size: 1.08rem; }
  .pillar-list { list-style: none; margin: 2rem 0 0; padding: 0; display: grid; gap: 0; }
  .pillar-list li {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    padding: 1.6rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-line);
  }
  .pillar-list li:last-child { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-line); }
  .pillar-n {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    color: var(--color-clay);
    line-height: 1;
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 40;
  }
  .pillar-list h3 { font-size: 1.3rem; margin: 0 0 0.4rem; }
  .pillar-list p { margin: 0; color: var(--color-ink-soft); max-width: 48rem; }
  .text-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .start { margin-top: 4.5rem; }
  .start > h2 { font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.6rem); margin: 0.4rem 0 0; }
  .start-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }
  @media (min-width: 760px) { .start-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); } }
  .start-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    background: var(--color-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-line);
    border-radius: 0.8rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: border-color 0.18s var(--ease-out), transform 0.18s var(--ease-out),
      box-shadow 0.18s var(--ease-out);
  }
  .start-card:hover {
    border-color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--color-pine) 40%, var(--color-line));
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 14px 30px -20px rgba(33, 28, 21, 0.35);
  }
  .start-for {
    font-size: 0.76rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-clay);
  }
  .start-title { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-ink); line-height: 1.2; }
  .start-body { color: var(--color-ink-soft); font-size: 0.96rem; }
  .start-actions { display: flex; gap: 0.9rem; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 2rem; }
</style>
